Lafarge’s Bamburi Cement Unit in Kenya Says Pretax Profit Advances 22%

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-08-24T13:17:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/lafarge-s-bamburi-cement-unit-in-kenya-says-pretax-profit-advances-22-.html
Bamburi Cement Co., the Kenyan unit
of  Lafarge SA (LG) , said first-half pretax profit advanced 22 percent
from a year earlier.  Pretax earnings in the six months through June rose to 4.3
billion shillings ($47 million), the Nairobi-based company said
in an e-mailed statement today. Sales increased 26 percent to
16.4 billion shillings, the company said.  Athi River Mining Ltd. (ARML) ,  Kenya ’s second-biggest cement maker
by market value, said on Aug. 8 that first-half net income
climbed 27 percent to 441.9 million shillings in the six months
through June.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  